Emily Beisel is a renowned rodeo contestant, particularly known for her skills in barrel racing. She hails from Weatherford, Oklahoma, and has qualified for the Wrangler National Finals Rodeo (NFR) five times, starting the 2023 NFR in 3rd place.

Here you can follow Emily Beisel’s net worth, career earnings, professional career, achievements, relationship status, and more.

About Emily Beisel

Emily Beisel’s exact date of birth remains undisclosed, but she is estimated to be between 25 and 30 years old as of 2023. She hails from Weatherford, Oklahoma.

Emily grew up in a non-rodeo family in Southwest Kansas, but her love for horses and other animals was evident from an early age.

She is married to Austin Beisel, and the couple works hard to balance their rodeo world with their everyday life.

Professional Career

Beisel has had a successful career in rodeo, with several notable achievements. She won $15,000 at the Ram National Circuit Finals Rodeo, which was the second-best among all Women’s Professional Rodeo Association (WPRA) barrel racers.

She also won the Beef Empire Days Rodeo in Garden City, Kansas. In 2022, she and her horse Chongo placed in the first round of the NFR and she shared a win with Brittany Pozzi Tonozzi in Round Six of the Wrangler NFR.

She was also recognized in Cowgirl Magazine’s 30 Under 30 in 2021.

Emily Beisel’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Emily Beisel’s estimated net worth is $2 million.

Her successful career in rodeo and barrel racing has undoubtedly earned her significant income.

Career Earnings

Emily Beisel has had a successful career in rodeo, earning significant prize money from various events. She won $15,000 at the Ram National Circuit Finals Rodeo, which was the second-best among all Women’s Professional Rodeo Association (WPRA) barrel racers.

At the Fort Worth Stock Show & Rodeo, she earned $8,640, and at the San Antonio Rodeo, she won $6,500.

In 2023, Beisel had a particularly successful period over Cowboy Christmas, where she won a total of $25,277, which propelled her into the top rankings.

She also had a notable win at the 2023 Governor’s Cup, where she and her horse, Ivory On Fire, earned $43,250.

As of 2022, Beisel was in the 9th spot in the WPRA World Standings with total earnings of $93,964.

By the end of 2021, she was a career earner of $535,317 in the WPRA, and she added $59,640 to that total at the Wrangler National Finals Rodeo in Las Vegas.

Personal Details

Husband

Emily Beisel is married to Austin Beisel. The couple tied the knot in October 2020.

Austin Beisel’s surname is pronounced, “Buy-Sell”. They currently reside together, with Emily balancing her rodeo world with her everyday life.

How Old is Emily Beisel?

Her exact age is not publicly disclosed, but she is estimated to be between 25 and 30 years old as of 2023.

What is her nationality?

She is American.

Career Highlights

  • World titles: 0
  • Wrangler NFR qualifications: 3 (2019-21)
  • RNCFR qualifications (actual year qualified): 3 (2015-16, 2020)
  • RNCFR titles: 1 (2017)
